article.headline: St. Peter's 72, Monmouth, N.J. 62
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) -- Todd Sowell scored 23 points and pulled down 18 rebounds to lead St. Peter's to its third straight victory, a 72-62 win over Monmouth on Wednesday night. Nick Leon added 18 points for the Peacocks (3-2), while Raul Orta had 12 points and 10 rebounds. Jhamar Youngblood had a game-high 25 points for Monmouth (2-4), which only made 37 percent of its shots from the floor. The teams traded baskets for most of the first half, with the Peacocks holding a 36-32 lead at halftime. St. Peter's then tried to pull away in the second half, but the Hawks hung tough and cut the lead to 66-62 when Youngblood made two free throws with 2:10 left to play. The Hawks would not score again, though, and the Peacocks -- who only made three baskets over the final nine minutes -- sealed the win by making six foul shots in the final minute.
